  "text": "HomeShoppingBrand BioIt derives its name from the word \"Parevartan,\" which means \"transformation\" in Sanskrit.Photo: Courtesy of Parëva BeautyBrand Bio is Fashionista's guide to the best independent fashion and beauty brands — a resource for retailers, job seekers, B2B companies and consumers alike. If you'd like your brand to be featured, fill out this form.Parëva BeautyHeadquarters: New Jersey/New YorkE-commerce: parevabeauty.comSocial Media: Instagram / FacebookWhat: A \"clinically-crafted\" skin-care brand offering a minimalist three-step process to streamline beauty routines.Price Range: $49 - $112Founder: Smitha RaoOrigin Story: Parëva is a skin-care brand for people of all ages who are looking for products that provide clinically proven results and are \"joyfully simple.\" Parëva's name is a shortening of the word Parevartan, which means \"transformation\" in Sanskrit. Parëva was founded in 2024 by Smitha Rao, who has worked with more than 15 brands (including Strivectin, Sugarbear, Firefly, Dr. Kellyann and Olaplex) in the beauty and wellness space during her 18+ year career.Scroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesParëva products aim to transform not only how people care for their skin, but \"how they feel at every stage of life.\" With its Molecur 3 technology made in Switzerland and its products manufactured in the U.S., Parëva seeks to extend skin health for those seeking \"radical transparency and good science.\"Photo: Courtesy of Parëva BeautyHero Products: C35.5 Firming Glow Serum ($74) and RH5.5 Hydrabond Primer ($49)PR Representation: Society MarcomsHow to get in contact: Contact formWant your brand featured? Hit the link below.Please note: Occasionally, we use affiliate links on our site. This in no way affects our editorial decision-making.Fashionista's audience includes 1 million site visitors, 110,000 newsletter subscribers and 4.74 million social media followers. Want to know how to reach them? Learn more.Subscribe to Our Newsletter